The paper deals with synchronization strings, a combinatorial object that has applications in various communication settings, including coding theory and interactive coding schemes. The paper presents new explicit constructions and local decoding algorithms for synchronization strings, which are relevant to the areas of data structures (cs.DS), information theory (cs.IT), computational complexity (cs.CC), computational geometry (cs.CG), and discrete mathematics (cs.DM).
